    "spell": {
        "name": "Parch",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "text": "Dry winds dehydrate a creature. The target must attempt a Fortitude save; if used on a creature that has the water trait or a creature made primarily of liquid (such as many oozes), the creature uses the outcome for one degree of success worse than the result. Creatures whose bodies contain no significant moisture (such as earth elementals) are immune to parch. If a creature affected by *parch* drinks a liquid, such as a swig of water or a potion, the spell ends. Affected creatures that have the water trait or are made primarily of liquid, as well as affected creatures that can\u2019t drink, can end the effect as a two-action activity, which has the concentrate trait.",
        "subtype": "spell",
        "spell_type": "focus",
        "rank": 1,
        "traits": [
